VALUES
(42, 6, 42, 20, 18, 17, 17, 'hypocrite, cast out first the beam', 'Judgment and Self-Reflection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of self-examination before judging others. Luke 6:42 warns against hypocrisy, while Proverbs 18:17 suggests that one''s own perspective may seem just until challenged by others.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 42, 40, 26, 75, 75, NULL, 'Hypocrisy and Self-Reflection', 'This connection highlights the theme of self-awareness and hypocrisy. In Luke, Jesus calls out hypocrisy in judging others, while in Matthew, Peter''s denial reflects a moment of painful self-realization.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 42, 42, 13, 15, 15, 'hypocrite', 'Hypocrisy and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of hypocrisy, where individuals are criticized for failing to recognize their own faults before judging others. In Luke 6:42, the focus is on the hypocrisy of pointing out minor faults in others while ignoring one''s own significant issues, while Luke 13:15 highlights the hypocrisy of prioritizing animal care over human needs on the Sabbath.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 43, 24, 2, 21, 21, 'good tree bringeth not forth corrupt fruit', 'Fruitfulness and Degeneration', 'This connection highlights the theme of fruitfulness and the nature of plants. Both passages emphasize the transformation of a good plant into a degenerate one, illustrating the consequences of moral and spiritual decline.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 43, 40, 12, 33, 33, 'good tree bringeth not forth corrupt fruit', 'Fruit and Tree Analogy', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the quality of a tree and its fruit. They highlight that a good tree produces good fruit, while a corrupt tree produces corrupt fruit.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 43, 40, 7, 16, 20, NULL, 'Connection of Good and Corrupt Trees', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between trees and their fruits, illustrating that a good tree produces good fruit while a corrupt tree produces evil fruit. This connection highlights the importance of discernment based on the outcomes of one''s actions.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 43, 19, 92, 12, 14, NULL, 'Fruitfulness of Righteousness', 'Both passages emphasize the idea that good trees produce good fruit, paralleling the flourishing of the righteous who bring forth fruit in old age. This connection highlights the theme of righteousness leading to positive outcomes.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 43, 23, 5, 4, 4, NULL, 'Fruitfulness and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the outcome of a tree or vineyard based on its nature. Luke highlights that a good tree cannot produce bad fruit, while Isaiah laments that his vineyard produced wild grapes despite his efforts.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 43, 23, 61, 3, 3, 'good tree bringeth not forth corrupt fruit', 'Connection of Righteousness and Fruitfulness', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of trees symbolizing righteousness and the fruit they bear. Luke highlights that a good tree produces good fruit, while Isaiah describes those who are righteous as ''trees of righteousness,'' indicating a direct relationship between one''s nature and the outcomes they produce.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 44, 40, 12, 33, 33, NULL, 'Fruit and Tree Connection', 'Both passages emphasize that a tree is known by its fruit, illustrating the relationship between the nature of the tree and the quality of its produce. This connection highlights the idea that good or corrupt fruit reflects the inherent character of the tree.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 44, 59, 3, 12, 12, 'every tree is known by his own fruit', 'Fruitfulness and Consistency', 'Both passages emphasize that a tree is known by its fruit, illustrating the principle that one cannot produce different kinds of fruit. This connection highlights the consistency required in character and actions.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 44, 48, 5, 19, 23, 'by his own fruit', 'Connection of Fruit and Works', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of fruit as a reflection of one''s nature. Luke 6:44 discusses how trees are known by their fruit, while Galatians 5:19-23 contrasts the works of the flesh with the fruit of the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 44, 56, 2, 11, 13, 'known by his own fruit', 'Connection of Righteous Living', 'This connection highlights the importance of the outcomes of one''s life. Just as a tree is known by its fruit, the teachings in Titus emphasize living righteously and godly, which reflects the fruit of grace in a believer''s life.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 44, 65, 1, 12, 12, 'every tree is known by his own fruit', 'Connection of Fruit Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of trees and their fruit, illustrating the idea that the quality of fruit reflects the nature of the tree. Luke highlights that trees are known by their fruit, while Jude describes trees whose fruit withers, indicating a lack of true nourishment.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 45, 20, 4, 23, 23, NULL, 'Heart and Its Influence', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of the heart in determining one''s actions and words. Luke 6:45 highlights that the mouth speaks from the heart''s abundance, while Proverbs 4:23 stresses the need to guard the heart, as it influences the issues of life.', 'theme', 0.6639999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 45, 40, 12, 34, 37, 'for of the abundance of the heart his mouth speaketh', 'Connection of Heart and Speech', 'Both passages emphasize that ''out of the abundance of the heart the mouth speaketh,'' linking the condition of the heart to the words spoken. They also highlight the distinction between good and evil men based on what they produce from their hearts.', 'theme', 0.601, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 45, 49, 4, 29, 29, 'of the abundance of the heart', 'Connection of Speech and Heart', 'This connection highlights the relationship between the heart and speech. Both passages emphasize that what comes out of the mouth reflects the condition of the heart, whether good or corrupt.', 'theme', 0.594, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 45, 43, 7, 38, 38, NULL, 'Connection of Heart and Belief', 'This connection highlights the relationship between the inner state of a person and their outward expression. Both passages emphasize that what is within, whether good or evil, influences what flows out, whether it be words or living water.', 'theme', 0.5449999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 45, 19, 37, 30, 31, 'of the abundance of the heart his mouth speaketh', 'Connection of Heart and Speech', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the heart and speech. Luke highlights that ''of the abundance of the heart his mouth speaketh,'' while Psalms states ''the law of his God is in his heart,'' suggesting that what is in one''s heart influences their words.', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 45, 19, 59, 12, 12, 'of the abundance of the heart his mouth speaketh', 'Connection of Speech and Heart', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the heart and speech. Luke 6:45 discusses how the heart influences what one speaks, while Psalms 59:12 addresses the consequences of sinful words from the mouth.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 45, 51, 3, 16, 16, NULL, 'Connection of Heart and Speech', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of what resides in the heart. Luke 6:45 discusses how the heart influences speech, while Colossians 3:16 encourages singing with grace in your hearts, suggesting that the heart''s condition affects one''s expressions.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 46, 48, 6, 7, 7, 'do not the things which I say', 'Obedience and Consequences', 'This connection highlights the importance of aligning actions with one''s declarations. Both passages emphasize that calling Jesus ''Lord'' requires obedience, and that one''s actions will determine the outcomes they face.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 46, 39, 1, 6, 6, 'Lord, Lord, and do not the things which I say', 'Honor and Obedience to Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of honoring authority figures. Both passages emphasize the expectation of obedience and respect towards God, as seen in the call to do what He says and the question of where His honor is.', 'theme', 0.482, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 46, 40, 7, 21, 23, 'Lord, Lord', 'Connection of Lordship and Obedience', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of doing the will of God rather than merely professing faith. The phrase ''Lord, Lord'' appears in both, highlighting the distinction between verbal acknowledgment and genuine obedience.', 'theme', 0.482, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 46, 42, 13, 25, 27, 'Lord, Lord', 'Lordship and Obedience Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of true obedience to Jesus as Lord. In Luke 6:46, calling Him ''Lord'' is questioned without action, while in Luke 13:25-27, those who call ''Lord, Lord'' are rejected for not being known by Him due to their iniquity.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 46, 40, 25, 44, 44, 'Lord, Lord', 'Obedience to the Lord', 'This connection highlights the importance of actions reflecting one''s acknowledgment of Jesus as Lord. Both passages emphasize the necessity of doing what the Lord commands, particularly in serving others.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 46, 43, 13, 13, 17, 'do not the things which I say', 'Obedience to Christ''s Example', 'This connection highlights the importance of doing what Jesus commands. Both passages emphasize the relationship between calling Him ''Lord'' and acting according to His teachings.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 47, 59, 1, 22, 25, 'doeth them', 'Connection of Action and Hearing', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of not just hearing the word but also doing it. Luke speaks of those who ''doeth them,'' while James warns against being ''hearers only.''', 'theme', 0.538, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 47, 40, 7, 24, 27, 'heareth my sayings, and doeth them', 'Connection of Wisdom and Action', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of hearing and doing Jesus'' sayings. They illustrate the consequences of one''s actions through the metaphor of building on rock versus sand.', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 47, 42, 11, 28, 28, 'heareth my sayings, and doeth them', 'Hearing and Keeping God''s Word', 'This connection highlights the importance of both hearing and acting upon God''s teachings. Both passages emphasize the blessedness of those who hear and keep the word of God.', 'theme', 0.503, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
